var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"location":"#JSWAP.jl","page":"Home","title":"JSWAP.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for JSWAP","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The main target of JSWAP is to provide an easy-to-use parallelization finite-difference wavefield simulation in heterogenous media. As all of the dependencies have been added to JSWAP, it is easy to install and deploy in another computer, even to clusters. The tutorial gives details for the input, output, utilities and structure of the package.","category":"page"},{"location":"Utilities/#Utilities","page":"Utilities","title":"Utilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Utilities/","page":"Utilities","title":"Utilities","text":"JSWAP.meshgrid\nJSWAP.write2mat\nJSWAP.readmat\nJSWAP.rickerWave","category":"page"},{"location":"Utilities/#JSWAP.meshgrid","page":"Utilities","title":"JSWAP.meshgrid","text":"Same with meshgrid in Matlab\n\nX,Y=meshgrid(x,y) returns 2-D grid coordinates based on the coordinates contained in vectors x and y. X is a matrix where each row is a copy of x, and Y is a matrix where each column is a copy of y. The grid represented by the coordinates X and Y has length(y) rows and length(x) columns.\n\nX,Y,Z=meshgrid(x,y,z) returns 3-D grid coordinates defined by the vectors x, y, and z. The grid represented by X, Y, and Z has size length(y)-by-length(x)-by-length(z).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Utilities/#JSWAP.write2mat","page":"Utilities","title":"JSWAP.write2mat","text":"write a mat file.\n\nExample: write2mat(path,var).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Utilities/#JSWAP.readmat","page":"Utilities","title":"JSWAP.readmat","text":"read a mat file.\n\nExample: readmat(path,var).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Utilities/#JSWAP.rickerWave","page":"Utilities","title":"JSWAP.rickerWave","text":"ricker wavelet.\n\nExample:rickerWave(frequency,dt,nt,magnitude).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"list_of_functions/#List-of-functions","page":"List of functions","title":"List of functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"list_of_functions/","page":"List of functions","title":"List of functions","text":"You can find all of the functions in JSWAP here.","category":"page"},{"location":"list_of_functions/","page":"List of functions","title":"List of functions","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"How_to_implement_forward/#Forward-simulation","page":"How to implement","title":"Forward simulation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"How_to_implement_forward/","page":"How to implement","title":"How to implement","text":"An example of the simulation implementation is given here. The main file is main_body.jl. Only one line is needed to change:","category":"page"},{"location":"How_to_implement_forward/","page":"How to implement","title":"How to implement","text":"path_to_input=[\"./input_template.jl\"];","category":"page"},{"location":"How_to_implement_forward/","page":"How to implement","title":"How to implement","text":"This line is used to tell JSWAP where the input file is. Multiple input files can be added. For instance,","category":"page"},{"location":"How_to_implement_forward/","page":"How to implement","title":"How to implement","text":"path_to_input=[\"./input_template.jl\",\"./input_template2.jl\",];","category":"page"},{"location":"How_to_implement_forward/","page":"How to implement","title":"How to implement","text":"Please navigate to the same path with main_body.jf before running it. Otherwise, some folders might not be found.","category":"page"},{"location":"How_to_implement_forward/","page":"How to implement","title":"How to implement","text":"The main file will go through the input file and the solver during the running, then outputs will be generated under the path specified in the input file. Only the main file is needed to run.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#Inputs","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"In JSWAP, all of the input parameters are assigned to a struct input2. The following input parameters are needed to run the simulation. Please go through one by one to check the input is correct.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-dt","page":"Inputs","title":"1. dt","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Time interval.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.dt=10.0^-3;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-dx,-dy,-dz","page":"Inputs","title":"2. dx, dy, dz","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Grid spacing in the x, y and z directions.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.dx=10.0;\ninput2.dy=10.0;\ninput2.dz=10.0;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-nt","page":"Inputs","title":"3. nt","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Time interval.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.nt=10.0^3;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-nx,-ny,-nz","page":"Inputs","title":"4. nx, ny, nz","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Grid points in the x, y and z directions.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.nx=80;\ninput2.ny=80;\ninput2.nz=90;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-X,Y,Z","page":"Inputs","title":"5. X,Y,Z","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: 3D true coordinate of the model.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float or Int.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [nx, ny, nz]","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.Y,input2.X,input2.Z=JSWAP.meshgrid(1:80,1:80,1:90);","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-Stiffness","page":"Inputs","title":"6. Stiffness","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Lame constants, &lambda; and &mu or stiffness matrix (Cij). Either of them is required for input.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [nx, ny, nz].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"# Lame constants for isotropic media\ninput2.lambda=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*1.0;\ninput2.mu=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*1.0;\n\n# Stiffness matrix for anisotropic media\ninput2.C11=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*3.0;\ninput2.C12=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*1.0;\ninput2.C13=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*1.0;\ninput2.C14=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C15=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C16=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*.5;\ninput2.C22=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*3.0;\ninput2.C23=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*1.0;\ninput2.C24=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C25=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C26=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*.5;\ninput2.C33=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*3.0;\ninput2.C34=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C35=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C36=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C44=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*1.0;\ninput2.C45=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C46=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C55=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*1.0;\ninput2.C56=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*0;\ninput2.C66=ones(80,80,90)*10^9*1.0;\n","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-rho","page":"Inputs","title":"7. rho","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Density.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [nx, ny, nz].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.rho=ones(80,80,90)*1000.0;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-inv_Qa","page":"Inputs","title":"8. inv_Qa","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Apparent attenuation.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [nx, ny, nz].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.inv_Qa=ones(80,80,90)*0.0;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-r1,-r2,-r3","page":"Inputs","title":"8. r1, r2, r3","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Grid locations of receivers in the x, y and z directions.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: Each of them is a 2-dimensional matrix, with the first direction to be 1 and the second direction as the number of receiver numbers.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Here is an example of 50 receivers.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.r1=zeros(Int32,1,50);\ninput2.r1[:]=30:79;\n\ninput2.r2=zeros(Int32,1,50);\ninput2.r2[:]=30:79;\n\ninput2.r3=zeros(Int32,1,50);\ninput2.r3 .=15;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-s1,-s2,-s3","page":"Inputs","title":"9. s1, s2, s3","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Grid locations of sources in the x, y and z directions.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: Each of them is a 2-dimensional matrix, with the first direction to be 1 and the second direction as the number of receiver numbers.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Here is an example of 2 sources.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.s1=zeros(Int32,1,2);\ninput2.s1[:] =[60 60];\n\ninput2.s2=zeros(Int32,1,2);\ninput2.s2[:] =[49 51];\n\ninput2.s3=zeros(Int32,1,2);\ninput2.s3[:] =[49 51];","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-Source-signals","page":"Inputs","title":"10. Source signals","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Source signal in each component. The source can be either directional source, P-wave source or moment-tensor source. There are 2 options:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"If one chooses directional source and P-wave source, the input is supposed to be input2.src1, input2.src2, input2.src3 and input2.srcp, corresponding to the source signals in the x, y, z directions and the P-wave components.\nIf moment tensor source is wanted, M11, M22, M33, M23, M13 and M12 are desired.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimensions: [nt, number of sources].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-r1t,-r2t,-r3t","page":"Inputs","title":"11. r1t, r2t, r3t","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Receiver true locations in the x, y and z directions.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32 or Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [1, number of receivers].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example of computation true locations based on above information.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.r1t=input2.r1*input2.dx;\ninput2.r2t=input2.r2*input2.dy;\ninput2.r3t=input2.r3*input2.dz;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-Rm","page":"Inputs","title":"12. Rm","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: One can mute some receivers with this option. 0 - mute, 1 - unmute.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32 or Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [number of receivers, component].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Component: 1 - x component, 2 - y component, 3 - z component, 4 - pressure component.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"If one does not want to mute any receivers, then","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.Rm=ones(length(input2.r3),4);","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-s1t,-s2t,-s3t","page":"Inputs","title":"13. s1t, s2t, s3t","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Source true locations in the x, y and z directions.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32 or Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [1, number of sources].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Here is an example of 50 receivers.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.s1t=input2.s1*input2.dx;\ninput2.s2t=input2.s2*input2.dy;\ninput2.s3t=input2.s3*input2.dz;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-lp","page":"Inputs","title":"14. lp","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: PML layers.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"For a 10 layer PML,","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.lp=10;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-nPML","page":"Inputs","title":"15. nPML","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: power of PML, normally 2.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.nPML=2;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-Rc","page":"Inputs","title":"16. Rc","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: PML theoretical reflection coefficient.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Some common coefficients:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"PML layers (lp) Rc\n10 10.0^-1\n20 10.0^-2\n30 10.0^-3\n40 10.0^-4","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.Rc=.1;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-PML_active","page":"Inputs","title":"17. PML_active","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: One can set if PML at one edge is working. Each element of the 1 by 6 matrix means if the PML is activated on the edge in an order of xminus, xplus, yminus, yplus, zminus, zplus. \"0\" is deactivated and \"1\" is activated.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Float64.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [1, 6].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Example for only zminus PML is deactivated:","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.PML_active=[1 1 1 1 0 1];","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-path","page":"Inputs","title":"18. path","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Path of master branch on where to store the wavefield vtk and wavefield mat file. This must be a parent path of pathpic, pathmodel and pathwavefield, pathrec.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: String.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: NA.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.path=p3;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-path_pic","page":"Inputs","title":"19. path_pic","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Path to store wavefield snapshot vtk file. If one assign it \"nothing\", then no wavefield snapshot will be saved.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: String.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: NA.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.path_pic=string(input2.path,\"/pic\");\ninput2.path_pic=nothing;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-path_model","page":"Inputs","title":"20. path_model","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Path to store the model, including material parameters and source and receiver locations.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: String.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: NA.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.path_model=string(input2.path,\"/model\");","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-path_wavefield","page":"Inputs","title":"21. path_wavefield","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Path to store mat wavefield. No wavefield matfile will be stored if path_wavefield is \"nothing\".","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: String.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: NA.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.path_wavefield=string(input2.path,\"/wavefield\");","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-path_rec","page":"Inputs","title":"22. path_rec","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Path to store recordings.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: String.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: NA.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.path_rec=string(input2.path,\"/rec\");","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-plot_interval","page":"Inputs","title":"23. plot_interval","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: Plot frequency/interval of vtk file. \"0\" for saving nothing.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.plot_interval=100;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/#.-wavefield_interval","page":"Inputs","title":"24. wavefield_interval","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Explanation: How frequent the wavefield is saved. \"0\" for saving nothing.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Type: Int32.","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"Dimension: [].","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"input2.wavefield_interval=0;","category":"page"},{"location":"Inputs/","page":"Inputs","title":"Inputs","text":"An example of input file is given here.","category":"page"},{"location":"Outputs/#Outputs","page":"Outputs","title":"Outputs","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Outputs/","page":"Outputs","title":"Outputs","text":"After running the \"mainbody.jl\", a folder for output will be generated in the destination specified in the input file. For instance, the example \"template2momenttensors\" will have a folder called \"mainbody\", in which there are \"model\", \"pic\", \"rec\" and \"wavefield\" and \"timeinfo.pvd\". Each of them will be explained in details. ParaView is needed to visualize the model and the wavefield.","category":"page"},{"location":"Outputs/#.-model-setup","page":"Outputs","title":"1. model setup","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Outputs/","page":"Outputs","title":"Outputs","text":"The folder \"model\" contains \"materialproporties.vts\", which can be loaded to ParaView.  ![loadmodel](./pictures/loadmodel.png)  The source and receiver true locations are stored in \"source location.csv\" and \"receiver location.csv\", respectively. There are 3 columns for the locations. They are corresponding to x, y and z coordinates. The first row is the header. With the \"data to points\" filter in paraview, they can be visualized with dots in 3D.  ![tabletopoints](./pictures/tabletopoints.png)  Here is an overview of the model setup with source (red dots) and receiver (green dots).  ![modelsetup](./pictures/model_setup.png)","category":"page"},{"location":"Outputs/#.-Wavefield-animation","page":"Outputs","title":"2. Wavefield animation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Outputs/","page":"Outputs","title":"Outputs","text":"The file \"timeinfo.pvd\" is the conclusive file which tells the path of the wavefield snapshot (under \"./pic\") and the time. Loading \"timeinfo.pvd\" to paraview is a good way to visualize the wavefield.  (Image: wavefield)","category":"page"},{"location":"Outputs/#.-Wavefield-.mat-file","page":"Outputs","title":"3. Wavefield .mat file","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Outputs/","page":"Outputs","title":"Outputs","text":"If the wavefield is saved (check input file), then the folder \"wavefield\" contains the wavefield, including v1, v2, v3, sigmas11, sigmas22, sigmas33, sigmas23 and p.","category":"page"},{"location":"Outputs/#.-Seismogram","page":"Outputs","title":"4. Seismogram","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Outputs/","page":"Outputs","title":"Outputs","text":"The recording files are saved under the folder \"rec\".","category":"page"},{"location":"Outputs/","page":"Outputs","title":"Outputs","text":"rec_1.mat: seismogram x component.\nrec_2.mat: seismogram y component.\nrec_3.mat: seismogram z component.\nrec_p.mat: seismogram pressure component.","category":"page"},{"location":"Outputs/","page":"Outputs","title":"Outputs","text":"Structure of every file: first dimension - time dependent signals, second dimension - receiver number.","category":"page"},{"location":"Outputs/","page":"Outputs","title":"Outputs","text":"(Image: v1)  (Image: v2)  (Image: v3)  (Image: p)","category":"page"}]
}
